pull_request.title: Implement A-Z Fast Scroller with Opacity Effects for App List
pull_request.body:
This PR implements a Material Design A-Z fast scroller for the app list screen that allows users to quickly navigate through apps alphabetically. When interacting with the scroller, apps starting with the selected letter remain at full opacity while all other apps fade to 30% opacity for better visual focus.

## Features

### Custom FastScrollerView
- **Material Design Compliant**: Uses the app's existing red/black color scheme and follows Android design guidelines
- **Vertical A-Z Layout**: Displays all 26 letters in a compact vertical scroller positioned on the right edge
- **Visual Feedback**: Shows pressed state with rounded background and highlights selected letter
- **Smooth Touch Handling**: Responsive drag gestures for seamless letter selection

### Enhanced User Experience  
- **Opacity Effects**: Non-matching apps fade to 30% opacity during letter selection for improved focus
- **Smart Scrolling**: Automatically scrolls to the first app starting with the selected letter
- **Preserved Functionality**: Maintains existing search functionality and app locking features
- **Performance Optimized**: Efficient filtering and rendering without impacting list performance

### Technical Implementation
- **Zero Dependencies**: No changes to gradle files or external dependencies required
- **Custom View**: Extends Android's View class with custom drawing and touch event handling
- **Minimal Footprint**: Surgical changes to existing codebase preserving all current functionality
- **Resource Efficient**: Added only necessary dimensions and one background color

## Files Changed
- `FastScrollerView.kt` - New custom view implementing the A-Z scroller
- `fragment_app_list.xml` - Updated layout to include scroller in FrameLayout
- `AppListAdapter.kt` - Added letter filtering and opacity control
- `AppListFragment.kt` - Integrated scroller touch events and scrolling behavior
- `dimens.xml` - Added scroller dimensions (32dp width, 12sp text)
- `colors.xml` - Added semi-transparent background color

The implementation provides an intuitive way for users to quickly navigate through large app lists while maintaining the app's visual consistency and performance standards.

issue.title: Crash if tray icon used on Windows 10
issue.body:
### Flameshot Version

Flameshot v13.0.1 (48f8d1fd)
Compiled with Qt 6.8.1
winnt: 10.0.19045
windows: 10

### Installation Type

Linux, MacOS, or Windows Package manager (apt, pacman, eopkg, choco, brew, ...)

### Operating System type and version

Windows 10

### Description

The tool does crash if the tray icon is used multiple times.

You will need to open up a popup menu with your first interaction otherwise it will keep running. In theory it does not matter which dialog you open the behavior is always identically.

### Steps to reproduce

1. Right click tray icon
2. Select about Flameshot
3. Close popup menu
4. Right click tray icon again
5. Flameshot crashing without warning

### Screenshots or screen recordings

_No response_

### System Information

Windows 10 dual HD monitor setup

issue.title: I'm getting 3 errors of "image not found" and "status 400 when atempting to download", what am I doing wrong?
issue.body: basically the title, what am I doing wrong to get these? adding the log just in case. [meta (2).log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21823002/meta.2.log)

comment.body:
1. This image is always a pain to deal with because in the HTTP world, `#` is not a valid character and should be referenced in unicode (i.e. `%230.jpg`). I don't have a good solution for this and since the network is not well known, it's not a priority. It can be ignored.
2. I've added HBO Max to the network overlays, this is likely due to the re-rebrand of Max - 3f8e786
3. I don't yet have a Tubi overlay image to reference, so Kometa shows an error since it can't find it.

None of these are breaking changes but if you have shows using `#0` or `Tubi`, it won't add any overlay for them. I will try to put together a Tubi overlay sometime soon.

issue.title: writeValue sometimes does not return when sending multiple messages

comment.body:
> I tried making a fairly barebones CoreBluetooth client as well that just uses continuations to make it async and it had the same problem. I don't know if it's my peripheral or if there's some queuing or checking that i need to be doing

If your message has a write type `.withoutResponse`, it probably has something to do with `peripheralIsReady(toSendWriteWithoutResponse:)`, since this library doesn't handle that, it may cause hanging after setting complete for writeCharacteristicValueExecutor. For a typical CoreBluetooth application, it will handle that in a kind of loop of resending the data that `failed` since CoreBluetooth has no error callback for that type of message.

I‚Äôm trying to implement a Peripheral Manager in the same manner, maybe able to fix this along the way. Will update later.
